pageContext.claim: “Sweden has somewhat of a relationship with North Korea.  We’ve been working with North Korea.'
pageContext.analysis: This is an understatement. Sweden is one of the few western countries to maintain an embassy in Pyongyang. It provides consular services to the U.S. citizens in North Korea. The country has had diplomatic relations with North Korea since 1973. It has been rumored as one possible site for U.S.-North Korea talks.
